      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRIUMVIRATE (5) was well-backed in a metro maiden on debut but failed to flatter, after which he found his way to Lindsay Park. Had his first run for that camp in a rich maiden at Albury, closing off well to be beaten less than a length, which looks good enough form to measure up here. Mark Zahra riding from gate two certainly isn't a negative. TSAVO (6) is another who started life in NSW before coming to Victoria and after two nice placings for the new stable he found the Emerging Stars Final a little bit rich last time. Placed in two jumpouts since and can make an impression first-up. COL KLINK (1) also resumes and will find this more to his liking than the VOBIS Gold Carat, when he was only beaten 4 lengths. ONLOOKER (4) is on debut but has run top two at all four jumpouts, including a win at the latest, so could show up with blinkers on.",
